I met Larry Birkhead for the first time
when they all came to New York City.

01:20:34.746 --> 01:20:40.043
And Larry was there and… and kind of
introduced as her photographer…

01:20:40.126 --> 01:20:41.127
[inhales deeply]

01:20:41.211 --> 01:20:44.130
…but it was pretty obvious
that he was maybe more than that.

01:20:44.756 --> 01:20:48.718
And I also knew
that she was, at that time,

01:20:48.802 --> 01:20:51.763
kind of wanting to be pregnant
and to have a baby.

01:20:51.847 --> 01:20:55.183
So, my mind of course went there to,

01:20:55.267 --> 01:20:59.521
"Oh, this is probably
who she hopes will father her child."

01:20:59.604 --> 01:21:00.605
[camera shutter clicking]

01:21:01.189 --> 01:21:03.400
I was in LA for something,
and I went to visit.

01:21:03.483 --> 01:21:07.863
He was kind of there,
and they were trying to have a child.

01:21:07.946 --> 01:21:11.992
Um, but he wasn't staying in her room.
He was kind of… kind of had his own room.

01:21:12.576 --> 01:21:14.619
Um… [scoffing] …yeah.

01:21:14.703 --> 01:21:17.289
-[camera shutter clicks]
-[somber music playing]

01:21:17.998 --> 01:21:23.670
[Mitchell] But I heard the details
of what she was looking for in a father.

01:21:25.463 --> 01:21:28.425
Like, "You won't have visitation rights,
or be paid money,

01:21:28.508 --> 01:21:31.553
or be able to legally say
that the child is yours."

01:21:31.636 --> 01:21:34.389
There were some pretty strict parameters

01:21:34.472 --> 01:21:39.227
surrounding, um, you know,
her having a child with somebody.

01:21:43.607 --> 01:21:47.360
So I figured he was on that same page.

01:21:55.744 --> 01:21:56.745
[light switch clicking]

01:21:57.370 --> 01:21:58.455
[objects clattering]

01:22:01.708 --> 01:22:06.379
[man] In 2004,
I took over a practice in Studio City.

01:22:06.463 --> 01:22:08.256
[footsteps approaching]

01:22:08.340 --> 01:22:09.507
[door opening]

01:22:10.467 --> 01:22:11.468
[door closing]

01:22:12.344 --> 01:22:15.555
I was really not interested
in… in a celebrity practice.

01:22:15.639 --> 01:22:18.016
I mean, you know,
most of my patients were older.

01:22:19.100 --> 01:22:23.229
The doctor before me said,
"Have you heard of Anna Nicole Smith?"

01:22:23.313 --> 01:22:25.190
"I see her for chronic pain."

01:22:25.815 --> 01:22:27.943
"She's very, um, manipulative,

01:22:28.026 --> 01:22:32.656
and she's… and she can charm you and try--
Just don't get caught in that."

01:22:33.365 --> 01:22:35.158
[contemplative music playing]

01:22:35.241 --> 01:22:37.577
[Dr. Kapoor] She had had many ailments
over the past,

01:22:37.661 --> 01:22:41.289
including various things
like fibromyalgia.

01:22:41.373 --> 01:22:45.210
Um, uh, she'd had significant, like,
different back pains.

01:22:47.504 --> 01:22:49.255
She had some chest pain.

01:22:50.465 --> 01:22:53.593
A breast implant that was ruptured
and had to be repaired.

01:22:56.054 --> 01:23:01.768
And when there was, uh, emotional issues
that were happening to her,

01:23:01.851 --> 01:23:03.603
um, her pain was worse.

01:23:03.687 --> 01:23:04.562
[reporter] Anna.

01:23:04.646 --> 01:23:06.064
[reporters clamoring]

01:23:06.147 --> 01:23:07.816
[Dr. Kapoor] What you see
in the public eye

01:23:07.899 --> 01:23:10.819
is this bubbly, vivacious,

01:23:10.902 --> 01:23:13.822
uh, this, you know,
bombshell type of thing.

01:23:13.905 --> 01:23:16.366
But behind the scenes, um,

01:23:17.409 --> 01:23:19.077
it's a different story.

01:23:19.160 --> 01:23:20.495
[man laughing]

01:23:21.454 --> 01:23:22.789
[Dr. Kapoor] She was on methadone,

01:23:22.872 --> 01:23:25.667
which was the pain medicine
that worked for her.

01:23:27.293 --> 01:23:30.255
This is a medicine that is…
is, uh, always known

01:23:30.338 --> 01:23:33.049
as people that are addicted to heroin.

01:23:33.842 --> 01:23:36.803
So people would look at it and say,
"Well, she must've been a heroin addict."

01:23:43.685 --> 01:23:46.479
She said,
"Um, don't worry about the doses."

01:23:46.563 --> 01:23:49.607
"I'm like a horse.
I can take a lot of medicine."

01:23:51.901 --> 01:23:54.487
"It takes me a lot to have the effect."

01:23:59.617 --> 01:24:00.452
[dog barking]

01:24:00.535 --> 01:24:04.998
Hi, it's me, Anna Nicole, as you can see.

01:24:05.582 --> 01:24:08.293
I've been hearing a lot of gossip
in the papers.

01:24:08.376 --> 01:24:12.714
"Is Anna pregnant? She's pregnant.
She's pregnant by some guy."

01:24:14.174 --> 01:24:17.343
Well, let me stop all the rumors.

01:24:17.427 --> 01:24:20.055
Yes, I am pregnant.

01:24:20.889 --> 01:24:23.475
I, uh, I'm happy.

01:24:23.558 --> 01:24:25.351
I'm very, very happy about it.

01:24:25.435 --> 01:24:27.729
I'll let you see me as I'm growing.

01:24:27.812 --> 01:24:30.690
So, that's it at this time.

01:24:31.399 --> 01:24:32.233
Bye.

01:24:32.984 --> 01:24:34.360
[suspenseful music playing]

01:24:34.444 --> 01:24:36.821
So one day, Anna sent me an email,

01:24:36.905 --> 01:24:41.159
and she said,
"Guess what? You're gonna be an aunt!"

01:24:41.242 --> 01:24:42.702
[Mitchell laughing]

01:24:42.786 --> 01:24:47.624
So she said,
"Howard, you can be the father."

01:24:47.707 --> 01:24:49.084
"We'll do this together."

01:24:50.752 --> 01:24:52.462
Just think of how beautifully that worked.

01:24:52.545 --> 01:24:54.214
I mean, this is her attorney,

01:24:55.090 --> 01:24:56.841
who is a friend.

01:24:56.925 --> 01:24:58.927
You know, not a lover, but a friend.

01:24:59.010 --> 01:25:01.679
And, um… And they're going to--

01:25:01.763 --> 01:25:03.598
They have obviously a really strong bond,

01:25:03.681 --> 01:25:05.517
and they're gonna continue
to have a strong bond

01:25:05.600 --> 01:25:08.728
as they work together
through all kinds of legal challenges.

01:25:08.812 --> 01:25:14.692
So it made perfect sense
for that to be the ultimate storyline.

01:25:15.693 --> 01:25:18.571
I think my parents
were a little shocked. [laughing]

01:25:19.405 --> 01:25:20.365
You know, um…?

01:25:22.242 --> 01:25:25.995
Because Howard never, that I'm aware of,

01:25:26.079 --> 01:25:29.541
never said to my parents,
"I'm having a relationship with Anna."

01:25:29.624 --> 01:25:33.128
You know?
Like, I don't think they knew that.

01:25:35.171 --> 01:25:39.425
My mom, like, being a grandmother,
was, like, that was her pride and joy.

01:25:46.057 --> 01:25:47.475
[music fades]

01:25:47.559 --> 01:25:49.561
[sirens wailing]

01:25:55.066 --> 01:25:58.528
[Nathan] I was at my apartment
in West Hollywood.

01:25:59.320 --> 01:26:02.198
I'm having a Kylie Minogue
birthday party. [chuckling]

01:26:03.575 --> 01:26:07.162
I'm a huge Kylie fan,
so that day is very important to me,

01:26:07.245 --> 01:26:09.581
and I try to throw a party when I can.

01:26:11.374 --> 01:26:13.376
[electro-pop music playing]

01:26:14.210 --> 01:26:16.421
[Nathan] And just like every party
in Hollywood,

01:26:16.504 --> 01:26:18.965
there was alcohol, and there was cocaine,

01:26:19.048 --> 01:26:21.384
and we were just having a good time.

01:26:21.467 --> 01:26:23.094
[indistinct chatter]

01:26:24.012 --> 01:26:26.472
[Nathan] And Daniel comes over.

01:26:27.098 --> 01:26:31.186
"Hey. You wanna have a drink?"
He's like, "I wanna have everything."

01:26:31.269 --> 01:26:34.856
[chuckling] I was like,
"Where… Where did this come from?"

01:26:35.481 --> 01:26:36.733
[tense music playing]

01:26:36.816 --> 01:26:38.318
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

01:26:38.401 --> 01:26:40.403
[Nathan] Daniel never drank. [chuckling]

01:26:41.362 --> 01:26:42.906
I never saw him drink.

01:26:42.989 --> 01:26:48.661
Maybe, I mean, one beer
every two weeks or three weeks or…

01:26:48.745 --> 01:26:49.746
It was very rare.

01:26:50.955 --> 01:26:53.208
Fast-forward to May.

01:26:53.917 --> 01:26:55.001
He's drinking.

01:26:55.710 --> 01:26:59.130
He's doing cocaine. He's doing pills.

01:26:59.631 --> 01:27:01.841
He was… I think he was about to turn 21.

01:27:03.051 --> 01:27:07.639
Personality-wise,
I had noticed that he had…

01:27:09.557 --> 01:27:13.311
kind of changed.

01:27:13.394 --> 01:27:16.981
Like, it was a little bit more
of an edgier, darker side of Daniel

01:27:17.065 --> 01:27:18.358
that I hadn't seen before.

01:27:19.859 --> 01:27:23.238
I think… I think I offered him a drink,
and he was just like…

01:27:24.322 --> 01:27:27.575
He said, "Can I drink on some methadone?"

01:27:27.659 --> 01:27:30.245
And I was like, "Where did you get
the methadone?" [chuckles]

01:27:30.328 --> 01:27:34.666
I'm like, "Did you take it from your mom?"
And he said… He was like, "Yeah."

01:27:36.251 --> 01:27:40.004
I'm like, "First of all,
how much did you take?" [chuckling]

01:27:40.088 --> 01:27:42.548
He's like… He's like, "I just took one.
I just…"

01:27:43.341 --> 01:27:44.717
[Nathan sighing heavily]

01:27:45.343 --> 01:27:46.970
I mean, honestly… [chuckling]

01:27:47.053 --> 01:27:48.763
[inhales deeply]

01:27:48.846 --> 01:27:50.014
…it sounds stupid,

01:27:50.098 --> 01:27:54.811
because I was at a party
with cocaine and alcohol. [chuckles]

01:27:54.894 --> 01:27:58.398
"You shouldn't be doing methadone,
but here have some cocaine."

01:27:58.481 --> 01:27:59.983
Um, it…

01:28:00.066 --> 01:28:04.028
You know, it's just one of those things
like, "God, be careful. I can't…"

01:28:04.112 --> 01:28:07.448
You know, "Stop doing that,
but here have some cocaine." [chuckles]

01:28:08.533 --> 01:28:09.742
[sighing heavily]

01:28:12.787 --> 01:28:15.790
[Nathan] You know, young and dumb,
but I was really worried.

01:28:16.457 --> 01:28:17.959
[crowd cheering]

01:28:18.042 --> 01:28:20.044
[ominous music playing]

01:28:25.550 --> 01:28:26.551
[music fades]

01:28:26.634 --> 01:28:29.470
[anchor] Former Playboy Playmate
Anna Nicole Smith's bid

01:28:29.554 --> 01:28:32.056
to get part of her late husband's fortune
has new life today,

01:28:32.724 --> 01:28:36.477
thanks to a very unlikely group of allies,
the Supreme Court.

01:28:37.228 --> 01:28:41.149
[anchor 2] The high court has agreed
to hear the ex-Playboy model's case.

01:28:41.232 --> 01:28:44.569
She's claiming millions of dollars
from her dead husband's estate.

01:28:44.652 --> 01:28:45.987
[tense music playing]

01:28:46.070 --> 01:28:47.447
[computer chiming]

01:28:47.530 --> 01:28:51.367
Whenever I would be on, um, AOL,
I would see a box,

01:28:51.451 --> 01:28:54.370
people who were on there,
and her name was Hot Smoochie Lips.

01:28:54.454 --> 01:28:56.539
[computer trilling]

01:28:56.622 --> 01:28:58.833
[Mitchell] So Anna had sent me
an instant message,

01:28:58.916 --> 01:29:01.169
and she was referring to Larry.

01:29:01.711 --> 01:29:03.463
[keyboard clacking]

01:29:06.466 --> 01:29:07.383
[computer chiming]

01:29:09.635 --> 01:29:11.387
[keyboard clacking]

01:29:14.223 --> 01:29:15.141
[computer chiming]

01:29:17.268 --> 01:29:19.270
[computer chiming]

01:29:22.315 --> 01:29:23.232
[computer chiming]

01:29:23.316 --> 01:29:25.902
[Mitchell] It was really clear
that Anna Nicole did not want

01:29:25.985 --> 01:29:27.737
to share custody with somebody else.

01:29:27.820 --> 01:29:30.531
She just wanted the child,
no strings attached,

01:29:30.615 --> 01:29:34.452
and the best way to do that
was to maybe escape the States

01:29:34.535 --> 01:29:36.079
and… and do this elsewhere.

01:29:45.505 --> 01:29:47.173
[music fades]

01:29:48.341 --> 01:29:50.635
[Pol'] Anna never wanted anything
from Larry.

01:29:51.552 --> 01:29:53.471
Anna wanted Larry to leave her alone.

01:29:56.557 --> 01:29:57.767
The truth is

01:29:59.060 --> 01:30:00.520
she couldn't stand him.

01:30:02.438 --> 01:30:05.024
-[melancholy music playing]
-[seagulls warbling]

01:30:17.036 --> 01:30:19.247
[Mitchell] The Bahamas
would be her fresh start.

01:30:19.330 --> 01:30:22.917
This was her chance
to raise the baby all by herself…

01:30:26.003 --> 01:30:28.506
and do it the way
that she wanted it to be done

01:30:28.589 --> 01:30:31.259
and the way she wished
she could've done for Daniel.

01:30:44.063 --> 01:30:49.652
In the Bahamas, there is, um,
a few interesting legalities.

01:30:50.528 --> 01:30:51.863
One being that

01:30:51.946 --> 01:30:57.118
whoever signed the birth certificate
in the Bahamas is the father.

01:30:57.201 --> 01:30:59.203
That's how they see it.

01:30:59.829 --> 01:31:04.375
And so if Howard K. Stern signs that,
then he's the legal father. The end.

01:31:11.090 --> 01:31:14.218
[Dr. Kapoor] Anna called me
in late August,

01:31:15.136 --> 01:31:19.891
and she had just informed me on the phone
that she has moved to the Bahamas.

01:31:27.190 --> 01:31:29.901
And I said, "Well what about your care…
you know, care?"

01:31:29.984 --> 01:31:33.321
"Um, well, I'm… I'm here,
and it's a beautiful place,

01:31:33.404 --> 01:31:35.490
and it's really relaxing,"
and all this stuff.

01:31:35.573 --> 01:31:37.366
I said, "Well, you know--"

01:31:37.450 --> 01:31:40.745
And then,
she also was calling really to say,

01:31:40.828 --> 01:31:42.997
"I'm gonna run out of my methadone."

01:31:43.080 --> 01:31:44.582
[seagulls warbling]

01:31:45.500 --> 01:31:50.129
[Dr. Kapoor] That can result
in withdrawals, which can be deadly,

01:31:50.213 --> 01:31:51.881
and I was worried about the baby.

01:31:53.382 --> 01:31:55.551
And I checked to see

01:31:55.635 --> 01:31:59.972
if, you know, you could even get methadone
in the Bahamas,

01:32:00.056 --> 01:32:01.599
and there was absolutely no way.

01:32:03.518 --> 01:32:06.103
So I called the pharmacy.

01:32:06.187 --> 01:32:09.899
"She needs to have this medicine.
She only has a couple of days left."

01:32:09.982 --> 01:32:11.234
I said, "What can I do?"

01:32:11.317 --> 01:32:12.443
[somber music playing]

01:32:12.527 --> 01:32:13.778
So the decision was made.

01:32:13.861 --> 01:32:19.116
We're going to try to get it
to her in the Bahamas from here.

01:32:20.034 --> 01:32:22.203
And, um, she got her methadone.

01:32:24.664 --> 01:32:26.624
And then, Daniel came to see me

01:32:26.707 --> 01:32:30.503
and was saying that he
and his mother were not getting along.

01:32:31.796 --> 01:32:37.927
He seemed anxious
and somewhat irritated by the situation.

01:32:39.929 --> 01:32:42.932
And he was struggling
with some issues of depression.

01:32:43.558 --> 01:32:48.563
And so he ended up being admitted
to a hospital.

01:32:49.230 --> 01:32:50.940
He was seen by a psychiatrist

01:32:51.023 --> 01:32:55.528
who started him on the medicine Lexapro
before he was discharged home.

01:32:55.611 --> 01:32:57.238
[ominous music playing]

01:32:57.989 --> 01:33:01.993
[Dr. Kapoor] I said, "You need
to come back and take care of him."

01:33:06.330 --> 01:33:09.500
I don't know if she realized
that, um, he was…

01:33:09.584 --> 01:33:12.169
the gravity of what he was going through.

01:33:12.253 --> 01:33:14.255
[unnerving music playing]

01:33:15.715 --> 01:33:17.717
[baby crying]

01:33:19.385 --> 01:33:20.344
[music fades]

01:33:20.428 --> 01:33:22.471
I was called by Howard

01:33:22.555 --> 01:33:26.392
and told that she just delivered
a bouncing baby girl,

01:33:27.268 --> 01:33:30.980
and she's, uh, she looks beautiful.

01:33:31.063 --> 01:33:33.357
And I… I said, "Can I speak to Anna?"

01:33:33.441 --> 01:33:38.446
She said, "Momo, the baby's beautiful
and all I ever… what I ever wanted."

01:33:38.529 --> 01:33:42.033
Then she told me, she says,
"Well, Daniel's on his way."

01:33:42.116 --> 01:33:44.493
Whew! Wow. Okay, we got them together.

01:33:44.577 --> 01:33:45.995
They're… They're talking.

01:33:51.292 --> 01:33:55.338
She sent the plane ticket,
and he's on his way.

01:33:56.964 --> 01:33:58.966
[somber music playing]

01:34:05.014 --> 01:34:06.849
[birds chirping]

01:34:09.810 --> 01:34:11.812
[seagulls warbling]

01:34:32.208 --> 01:34:33.668
[music fades]

01:34:33.751 --> 01:34:35.127
[phone ringing]

01:34:43.594 --> 01:34:44.679
[receiver clicking]

01:34:44.762 --> 01:34:46.514
[Maurice] I got
an out-of-state phone call,

01:34:46.597 --> 01:34:48.849
and I looked and said,
"Oh man, this is the Bahamas."

01:34:49.350 --> 01:34:55.314
And it was Howard on the phone,
very somber, soft, uh, tone in his voice.

01:34:55.398 --> 01:34:59.068
He said, "Uh, Mo, uh,
Anna needs you really bad."

01:34:59.151 --> 01:35:05.074
Then I could hear Anna in the background,
"Momo, come now! Momo, come now."

01:35:05.157 --> 01:35:07.535
So I… I said… I said, "What's going on?"

01:35:08.035 --> 01:35:10.162
He said, "Uh, Daniel just died."

01:35:10.913 --> 01:35:12.331
[waves crashing]

01:35:15.835 --> 01:35:17.044
[Maurice] I said, "What?

01:35:18.170 --> 01:35:19.755
What do you mean, 'just died'?"

01:35:20.464 --> 01:35:24.301
He said, "Yeah. He saw his sister,

01:35:24.385 --> 01:35:26.846
then never woke up."

01:35:26.929 --> 01:35:27.763
And…

01:35:29.223 --> 01:35:30.266
"He's gone."

01:35:33.978 --> 01:35:37.356
[spokesperson] Daniel Wayne Smith arrived
at the hospital late evening

01:35:37.440 --> 01:35:39.275
on Saturday, September 9th

01:35:40.109 --> 01:35:44.363
and remained as a visitor
with his mother and newly-born sister.

01:35:45.281 --> 01:35:49.493
On Sunday, at 9:38 a.m.,
the nurse was called,

01:35:50.119 --> 01:35:53.497
following which physicians on the floor
were immediately summoned.

01:35:53.581 --> 01:35:55.124
[somber music playing]

01:35:55.207 --> 01:35:59.003
[spokesperson] Resuscitative efforts using
advanced life-support protocol

01:35:59.086 --> 01:36:01.005
continued for 22 minutes.

01:36:02.256 --> 01:36:04.842
He was pronounced dead at 10:05 a.m.

01:36:06.218 --> 01:36:09.847
We would like to extend
our sincerest condolences

01:36:09.930 --> 01:36:13.100
to the family and the friends
of Daniel Wayne Smith,

01:36:13.768 --> 01:36:15.603
and we encourage the press

01:36:15.686 --> 01:36:18.773
to please be sensitive
to the family's loss

01:36:18.856 --> 01:36:23.068
and give them the opportunity
to grieve during this time.

01:36:30.785 --> 01:36:31.994
[Pol'] She was a wreck.

01:36:33.412 --> 01:36:34.830
She was incoherent.

01:36:35.331 --> 01:36:36.582
She couldn't talk.

01:36:38.751 --> 01:36:40.085
She didn't wanna live.

01:36:41.754 --> 01:36:45.132
Daniel was the reason
why she wanted to get out of Mexia, Texas.

01:36:47.510 --> 01:36:49.720
Everything that she did was for Daniel.

01:36:54.266 --> 01:36:56.644
[somber music continues]

01:37:09.448 --> 01:37:13.202
[Pol'] Every single conversation
was what she did wrong,

01:37:13.285 --> 01:37:15.079
blamed herself the whole time.

01:37:17.998 --> 01:37:18.874
[music fades]

01:37:18.958 --> 01:37:20.668
She said, "I just wanna die."

01:37:22.336 --> 01:37:25.631
"I don't deserve to be here.
It should've been me."

01:37:25.714 --> 01:37:27.424
"It should have never been him."

01:37:29.885 --> 01:37:31.470
[voice breaking] "It should've been me."

01:37:38.143 --> 01:37:42.356
Tonight, the sudden and unexpected death
of a young man, just 20 years old,

01:37:42.439 --> 01:37:43.732
under investigation.

01:37:44.775 --> 01:37:46.986
Twenty-year-old Daniel Smith,

01:37:47.069 --> 01:37:51.740
his death, his sudden and unexpected death
there in a Bahaman hospital,

01:37:51.824 --> 01:37:53.367
was it murder?

01:37:53.450 --> 01:37:55.911
[unnerving music playing]

01:37:55.995 --> 01:37:59.373
[anchor] Rumors continue to swirl
about the strange and sudden death

01:37:59.456 --> 01:38:01.417
of Anna Nicole Smith's son Daniel.

01:38:02.209 --> 01:38:04.545
As new evidence of an overdose emerges,

01:38:04.628 --> 01:38:09.049
we ask, could this be an accident
or even suicide?

01:38:09.133 --> 01:38:10.467
[camera shutters clicking]

01:38:10.551 --> 01:38:14.805
[Pol'] We're surrounded
with more than 300 paparazzi.

01:38:14.889 --> 01:38:21.770
The front and the side is barricaded
with photographers, international.

01:38:24.189 --> 01:38:27.359
Cameras sticking up over the wall…

01:38:28.861 --> 01:38:30.613
to see her devastation.

01:38:30.696 --> 01:38:32.698
[somber music playing]

01:38:33.741 --> 01:38:36.660
[Maurice] Every time she wakes up,
"Daniel's calling me."

01:38:37.244 --> 01:38:40.789
"Daniel wants me there.
Daniel wants me there."

01:38:43.584 --> 01:38:47.671
I would bring Dannielynn to her and said,
"This is the reason why you must live on."

01:38:48.964 --> 01:38:51.300
Her whole mentality would change.

01:38:52.593 --> 01:38:54.261
She would sit there, smile,

01:38:55.429 --> 01:38:57.848
and look at the baby, and say,
"You're just an angel."

01:38:57.932 --> 01:39:00.267
And I said,
"See, this is why you must live."

01:39:02.269 --> 01:39:06.106
But she wanted to be with Daniel
all the time.

01:39:10.736 --> 01:39:13.447
Because every time she would sleep,
she would see him.

01:39:13.530 --> 01:39:16.200
Mom! Mom!

01:39:17.868 --> 01:39:20.829
And that's why I believe
that she always liked to be sedated

01:39:20.913 --> 01:39:23.415
and taking these pills
that will help her sleep.

01:39:26.251 --> 01:39:28.337
Every dream, Daniel was there.

01:39:32.049 --> 01:39:36.845
Most of the people that was around her
was enabling her.

01:39:37.471 --> 01:39:40.641
She says, "Howard, I want you
to give me all these pills,

01:39:40.724 --> 01:39:44.687
and you either give them to me,
or I'll find somebody else that do."

01:39:45.270 --> 01:39:48.565
It ain't like Howard says,
"You have to take all these pills."

01:39:49.650 --> 01:39:51.068
Howard would never do that.

01:39:53.696 --> 01:39:55.364
She didn't need enablers.

01:40:03.414 --> 01:40:05.207
[anchor] This is a time of great joy
for her.

01:40:05.290 --> 01:40:07.418
She's bringing a new child into the world.

01:40:07.501 --> 01:40:09.670
And at the time of her greatest joy,

01:40:09.753 --> 01:40:12.214
something happens
to her 20-year-old child.

01:40:12.297 --> 01:40:15.342
That is going to make her
feel tremendously guilty.

01:40:28.480 --> 01:40:29.481
[music fades]

01:40:34.737 --> 01:40:36.739
[reporters clamoring]

01:40:36.822 --> 01:40:38.824
[camera shutters clicking]

01:40:39.908 --> 01:40:42.244
[Larry] Thanks, everybody, for coming.
And I just want to say

01:40:42.327 --> 01:40:45.414
that, um, I am the father of Dannielynn,

01:40:45.497 --> 01:40:47.666
and I think this is, um,

01:40:48.584 --> 01:40:51.253
a crime, basically,
what these people are doing to me.

01:40:51.336 --> 01:40:54.798
And I expect to be reunited
with my daughter,

01:40:54.882 --> 01:40:57.301
uh, with the help
of my attorney, Mrs. Opri.

01:40:57.384 --> 01:40:58.677
Thank you all for coming.

01:40:58.761 --> 01:41:01.722
[anchor] Who's the father
of Anna Nicole Smith's baby girl?

01:41:01.805 --> 01:41:04.600
If this man has anything to say about it,
it's him.

01:41:04.683 --> 01:41:07.102
[anchor 2] Dannielynn could inherit
millions of dollars

01:41:07.186 --> 01:41:12.024
from the estate of Smith's late husband,
oil tycoon J. Howard Marshall.

01:41:12.107 --> 01:41:14.068
[anchor 3] Why has Anna Nicole
been so secretive

01:41:14.151 --> 01:41:16.695
about who the father
of her new daughter is?

01:41:16.779 --> 01:41:21.784
Uh, Anna and I have, um,
been in a relationship,

01:41:21.867 --> 01:41:23.577
and we love each other,

01:41:23.660 --> 01:41:26.872
and it's been going on
for a very long time.

01:41:26.955 --> 01:41:28.290
So you are the father?

01:41:29.666 --> 01:41:30.501
Yes, sir.

01:41:31.418 --> 01:41:34.630
[Larry King] By the way, have there been
any DNA tests taken? Is that--

01:41:34.713 --> 01:41:36.799
-[Stern] Proud father.
-[Larry King] What?

01:41:37.466 --> 01:41:39.259
[Stern] I said, "Proud father."

01:41:39.343 --> 01:41:42.221
[anchor] Attorney Howard K. Stern says
he's the father.

01:41:42.304 --> 01:41:45.682
Ex-boyfriend Larry Birkhead says
the child is his,

01:41:45.766 --> 01:41:47.893
and in the zaniest moment of the day,

01:41:47.976 --> 01:41:51.355
Zsa Zsa Gabor's husband,
Prinz Frédéric von Anhalt,

01:41:51.438 --> 01:41:53.440
hinted even he could be involved.

01:41:54.024 --> 01:41:55.943
There are lots of people
who could be the father.

01:41:56.026 --> 01:41:57.236
[man] Could you be the father?

01:41:57.319 --> 01:41:58.654
I don't know. I mean…

01:42:00.197 --> 01:42:02.199
Sometimes I'm a bad boy. Yeah.

01:42:02.783 --> 01:42:04.743
Who is the father of Dannielynn?

01:42:05.869 --> 01:42:09.373
He's the father of her.

01:42:09.957 --> 01:42:10.999
[Larry] I am the father.

01:42:11.083 --> 01:42:13.502
You know, until science proves me wrong,
I am the father.

01:42:14.586 --> 01:42:16.713
[Stern] We really haven't been allowed
to grieve

01:42:16.797 --> 01:42:19.424
with the way
that this whole thing has been handled.

01:42:20.175 --> 01:42:21.885
And, you know, I…

01:42:22.469 --> 01:42:25.973
It's gonna be, uh, I think, a little while

01:42:26.056 --> 01:42:30.352
before, um, you know, we're gonna be able
to experience real happy moments.

01:42:39.945 --> 01:42:41.280
[music fades]

01:42:42.197 --> 01:42:43.740
[clock ticking]

01:42:47.161 --> 01:42:49.329
[phone line ringing]

01:42:53.792 --> 01:42:54.918
[dispatcher] Fire and rescue.

01:42:55.002 --> 01:42:56.753
[officer] Hi, this is Seminole Police.

01:42:56.837 --> 01:42:59.214
If you can please respond
to the Hard Rock.

01:42:59.298 --> 01:43:01.967
-[dispatcher] Uh-huh.
-[officer] Room 607.

01:43:02.050 --> 01:43:02.885
[dispatcher] Okay.

01:43:02.968 --> 01:43:06.471
[officer] It's gonna be in reference
to a white female, who is, um…

01:43:07.639 --> 01:43:09.308
What, is she not responsive?

01:43:09.391 --> 01:43:11.435
[officer 2] Not responsive
and not breathing.

01:43:11.518 --> 01:43:13.645
[officer] She's not breathing,
and she's not responsive.

01:43:13.729 --> 01:43:16.648
She's, um, actually Anna Nicole Smith.

01:43:16.732 --> 01:43:19.401
-[dispatcher] Oh, okay.
-[officer] Okay? All right. Thank you.

01:43:19.484 --> 01:43:21.486
[somber music playing]

01:43:27.701 --> 01:43:29.703
[inaudible]

01:44:14.706 --> 01:44:18.502
[Pol'] There's people
in front of the store going,

01:44:18.585 --> 01:44:22.172
"Do you know what's going on?
What happened? Did you hear?"

01:44:22.923 --> 01:44:26.051
And I'm like, "What are you talking about?
Who are you?"

01:44:26.551 --> 01:44:27.886
All these news vans.

01:44:29.346 --> 01:44:34.851
And Patrik goes… calls, uh,
Anna's number. She's not answering.

01:44:34.935 --> 01:44:37.646
Calls Howard. He's not answering.

01:44:37.729 --> 01:44:41.108
Calls Mo, and he goes,
"Baby girl is gone."

01:44:41.984 --> 01:44:43.694
Baby girl is gone."

01:44:43.777 --> 01:44:49.992
And the pain that he was speaking with
was so great.

01:44:51.368 --> 01:44:55.998
Run to the airport. First flight out.
Five hours later, we're in Florida.

01:44:58.250 --> 01:44:59.751
Howard was a mess.

01:45:00.377 --> 01:45:01.295
I mean,

01:45:02.713 --> 01:45:04.172
he was inconsolable.

01:45:05.257 --> 01:45:08.135
[anchor] A lot of people are really
painting Howard K. Stern as a villain.

01:45:08.218 --> 01:45:09.303
[man] How you doing today?

01:45:09.386 --> 01:45:12.347
[anchor] A lot of people have made him out
to be a manipulator.

01:45:12.431 --> 01:45:15.267
[anchor 2] Reportedly, they are looking
for possible prescriptions

01:45:15.350 --> 01:45:19.438
written out to Howard K. Stern
to supply Anna with drugs.

01:45:19.521 --> 01:45:22.899
Can you tell me why you're not cooperating
with the Broward County Medical Examiner?

01:45:22.983 --> 01:45:24.192
I have no comment to make.

01:45:24.276 --> 01:45:29.406
The methadone prescriptions
with my name on it appears in the press.

01:45:29.489 --> 01:45:33.994
This doctor shipped it over to her,
to a pregnant lady.

01:45:35.329 --> 01:45:38.123
And it… it felt like
they were blaming me for her death,

01:45:38.206 --> 01:45:41.001
um, and… and they were.

01:45:41.084 --> 01:45:42.836
[camera shutters clicking]

01:45:44.129 --> 01:45:45.505
[anchor] This may say a lot

01:45:45.589 --> 01:45:49.926
about our current culture
of celebrity and media these days

01:45:50.010 --> 01:45:53.263
when all the major cable news networks

01:45:53.347 --> 01:45:57.309
switched over to non-stop,
live coverage this afternoon,

01:45:57.392 --> 01:46:00.854
when word arrived
that Anna Nicole Smith had died.

01:46:00.937 --> 01:46:02.939
She was 39 years old.

01:46:03.023 --> 01:46:06.026
She was adored by millions
but loved by few.

01:46:06.610 --> 01:46:10.197
There was obviously always this sorta air
of tragedy around Anna Nicole Smith.

01:46:10.280 --> 01:46:12.199
She had so much misfortune in her life.

01:46:12.282 --> 01:46:14.284
[anchor] So what about Anna's money?

01:46:14.368 --> 01:46:18.914
Does she have a will,
and, um, who is the father of this child?

01:46:19.581 --> 01:46:21.500
Whoever has access to this child,

01:46:21.583 --> 01:46:25.545
whoever is raising this child has access
to whatever monies this child inherits,

01:46:25.629 --> 01:46:29.549
which is potentially tens of millions
if not hundreds of millions of dollars.

01:46:29.633 --> 01:46:33.136
I mean, the phrase "rest in peace"
means absolutely nothing, unfortunately,

01:46:33.220 --> 01:46:35.013
when it comes to Anna Nicole Smith.

01:46:35.097 --> 01:46:36.473
[inaudible]

01:46:49.694 --> 01:46:50.821
[music fades]

01:46:51.696 --> 01:46:55.075
[Missy] She told me all the time
that she was gonna die young.

01:46:57.285 --> 01:47:00.497
And I felt really bad because I said, I…
you know, I should've believed her.

01:47:00.580 --> 01:47:05.127
I should've, uh, spent some more time
doing things that were positive.

01:47:06.711 --> 01:47:09.256
I shouldn't have said
the stuff I said to her,

01:47:09.339 --> 01:47:11.591
you know, because now, I'm…
I can't take it back.

01:47:11.675 --> 01:47:13.844
I'm never gonna be able to change it.
It's… It's over.

01:47:13.927 --> 01:47:14.803
[Missy sniffling]

01:47:15.303 --> 01:47:18.598
And then I thought about her baby girl,
and I thought, "How sad."

01:47:18.682 --> 01:47:20.892
Because that little girl's
never gonna know

01:47:20.976 --> 01:47:24.521
how much her mother loved her
even before she was born, you know?

01:47:24.604 --> 01:47:27.983
She… She's never gonna know
how badly her mom wanted her,

01:47:28.066 --> 01:47:31.027
and she's never gonna feel
her hugging her,

01:47:31.111 --> 01:47:34.406
and… and singing to her, and doing
all those things that mothers do.

01:47:34.489 --> 01:47:36.491
[somber music playing]

01:47:42.914 --> 01:47:45.667
[Missy] But I thought, you know,
"At least, she's back with Daniel."

01:47:45.750 --> 01:47:49.212
"At least, her and Daniel
are back together," and… [sniffling]

01:47:51.548 --> 01:47:53.216
[inaudible]

01:47:57.262 --> 01:47:59.014
[camera shutters clicking]

01:48:23.413 --> 01:48:24.414
[music fades]

01:48:28.376 --> 01:48:30.378
[crow cawing]

01:48:34.799 --> 01:48:35.884
[dog barking]

01:48:55.987 --> 01:48:58.240
First of all, she's not my mother.

01:48:58.323 --> 01:48:59.866
She's my birth mother.

01:49:00.700 --> 01:49:02.369
[somber music playing]

01:49:08.166 --> 01:49:11.294
[Anna] I left home
when I was 15 years old.

01:49:12.420 --> 01:49:15.840
[Missy] I'm just sitting on the couch, uh,
and the TV's on.

01:49:15.924 --> 01:49:19.135
And I see Nicky on TV.

01:49:20.971 --> 01:49:24.558
What has she done for me?
You wanna hear how my childhood was?

01:49:25.600 --> 01:49:28.270
All the beatings,
and the whippings, and the rape.

01:49:29.145 --> 01:49:30.397
That's my mother.

01:49:31.273 --> 01:49:32.691
That's my mom.

01:49:32.774 --> 01:49:34.985
[Missy] She said
that she was raped at home,

01:49:35.068 --> 01:49:37.737
and she had to run away from home,
and she was beaten.

01:49:39.406 --> 01:49:40.615
Bitch.

01:49:41.199 --> 01:49:43.827
[Missy] I was shocked, because I knew

01:49:43.910 --> 01:49:46.496
that was not her childhood
coming out of her mouth.

01:49:46.580 --> 01:49:47.831
That was my childhood.

01:49:47.914 --> 01:49:50.542
That's exactly what happened to me
and the way I relayed it to her.

01:49:57.924 --> 01:50:02.178
Vickie told people
that my mama abused her.

01:50:03.555 --> 01:50:06.975
And she did not abuse her.

01:50:07.684 --> 01:50:11.396
My mother was a very sweet, loving person.

01:50:17.068 --> 01:50:19.529
[Missy] The only person
that I ever remember

01:50:19.613 --> 01:50:21.448
coming to her rescue was her mother,

01:50:21.531 --> 01:50:22.866
over and over and over.

01:50:23.700 --> 01:50:26.995
There were times that we got out of
a lot of trouble because of Virgie.

01:50:27.996 --> 01:50:31.082
If she had not been
in… in law enforcement,

01:50:31.166 --> 01:50:33.877
we… we would've been in prison
a couple times, you know?

01:50:36.504 --> 01:50:40.800
[Donald] They did talk to each other
behind the scenes.

01:50:42.802 --> 01:50:44.596
And they cared about each other.

01:50:48.433 --> 01:50:52.020
My mom passed away three years ago
with cancer.

01:50:53.813 --> 01:50:55.565
[birds chirping]

01:50:57.484 --> 01:50:58.943
[ominous music playing]

01:50:59.027 --> 01:51:00.320
We were not poor.

01:51:01.071 --> 01:51:04.032
We lived a moderate life in Houston.

01:51:08.495 --> 01:51:11.289
Three bedrooms, two carports.

01:51:18.129 --> 01:51:20.173
She would tell these stories

01:51:20.840 --> 01:51:23.009
about what a horrible

01:51:24.594 --> 01:51:26.012
childhood she had.

01:51:26.513 --> 01:51:28.264
And I said… I asked her one time. I said,

01:51:28.348 --> 01:51:31.935
"Vickie Lynn, why do you tell such lies?"

01:51:32.018 --> 01:51:33.103
"Why do you do that?"

01:51:33.728 --> 01:51:37.816
She said, "Mother, I wish
you could just understand that…

01:51:39.275 --> 01:51:44.614
I make more money telling sad stories

01:51:44.698 --> 01:51:47.242
than I make telling good stories."

01:51:47.325 --> 01:51:49.619
She… She said, "Don't get me wrong."

01:51:49.703 --> 01:51:53.581
"I make money
anytime my name is out in the open."

01:51:54.332 --> 01:51:56.459
"Anytime my name
is written down somewhere,

01:51:56.543 --> 01:51:59.045
in the newspaper, on TV, in the news."

01:51:59.129 --> 01:52:00.130
"It doesn't matter."

01:52:00.213 --> 01:52:03.425
"If my name is out there,
I'm making money."

01:52:04.426 --> 01:52:06.803
"Which is my purpose in life.
I'm making money."

01:52:07.303 --> 01:52:13.435
She said, "But if it's… if it's bad,
something really bad,

01:52:14.477 --> 01:52:20.191
I make 50 times the amount of money
than I make if it's good."

01:52:22.026 --> 01:52:26.197
And I said, "Well, Vickie, don't you want
people to think good about you?"

01:52:27.532 --> 01:52:29.993
She says, "Well, no.
Not if bad pays better."

01:52:31.536 --> 01:52:33.663
I said, "Doesn't it embarrass you?"

01:52:35.665 --> 01:52:39.544
She says, "No, not to the tune
of however much money I can make from it,

01:52:39.627 --> 01:52:40.795
it doesn't embarrass me."

01:52:40.879 --> 01:52:43.548
I said, "Don't you think
it embarrasses your family?"

01:52:46.050 --> 01:52:49.554
She says, "Mom… this is my life."

01:52:49.637 --> 01:52:50.680
[Virgie chuckling]

01:52:50.764 --> 01:52:53.308
"Not your life. This is my life."

01:52:53.391 --> 01:52:56.936
"So I ought to be able to tell
whatever stories I want to tell."

01:52:57.020 --> 01:52:59.230
"True or false,
I ought to be able to tell 'em."

01:53:02.734 --> 01:53:07.989
Nicky did very much get swept away
by a story that she created.

01:53:09.616 --> 01:53:11.993
Can you tell so many lies
and tell it so many times

01:53:12.076 --> 01:53:13.661
that all of a sudden it's true?

01:53:15.580 --> 01:53:20.001
But she lost her son.
She lost… She lost her life.

01:53:20.084 --> 01:53:21.753
She lost everything.

01:53:24.297 --> 01:53:26.132
That's what it cost her.

01:53:32.055 --> 01:53:33.181
[music fades]

01:53:34.891 --> 01:53:38.311
["My Heart Belongs to Daddy"
